body:
Hi All,

As per my requirement, i need to create a **SkTypeFace** of **Arial Narrow** font, to measure and draw the text with SkiaSharp.

When i try to create a "Arial Narrow" font directly with some default styles, SkiaSharp returns a type face of "Segeo UI". Similarly when i try to create a "Arial Narrow" font by mentioning a font name as "Arial" and SKFontStyleWidth as "Condensed", it returns a proper "Arial Narrow" font SkTypeFace. Please refer below code snippet for more clarifications.

My question is, **Is it a correct way to create a Narrow fonts SkTypeFace in SkiaSharp** ?

```
            // Create Arial Narrow font TypeFace with default styles.

            string fontName = "Arial Narrow";
            SKFontStyleWeight sKFontStyleWeight = SKFontStyleWeight.Normal;
            SKFontStyleSlant sKFontStyleSlant = SKFontStyleSlant.Upright;
            SKFontStyleWidth sKFontStyleWidth = SKFontStyleWidth.Normal;

            // Returns a TypeFace of default ("Segoe UI") font.
            SKTypeface skTypeface = SKTypeface.FromFamilyName(fontName, sKFontStyleWeight, sKFontStyleWidth, sKFontStyleSlant);

            // Create Arial Narrow font TypeFace by mentioning a font name as "Arial" and SKFontStyleWidth as "Condensed".

            // Sets a font name as "Arial".
            fontName = "Arial";
            // Sets a SKFontStyleWidth as "Condensed" to create a Narrow font.
            sKFontStyleWidth = SKFontStyleWidth.Condensed;

            // Returns a TypeFace of Arial Narrow font.
            skTypeface = SKTypeface.FromFamilyName(fontName, sKFontStyleWeight, sKFontStyleWidth, sKFontStyleSlant);
```

Thanks in advance.

Thanks,
M. Ramaraj.
